# ---   JSON/AJAX   ---
(only if/when you need it)

If you later POST JSON (no form), send the token in a header:

Header: X-CSRFToken (or X-CSRF-Token)

Value: {{ csrf_token() }}

cURL example:

curl -sk -b "$jar" -X POST "$BASE/some/json/endpoint" \
  -H "X-CSRFToken: $csrftoken" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"ok": true}'


#---   Exemptions (rare)   ---

For endpoints that must be POST but are public and machine-to-machine (e.g., webhooks), mark them exempt:

from app.extensions import csrf

@csrf.exempt
@bp.post("/webhook")
def webhook():
    ...

**  Keep exemptions to an absolute minimum.  **
